abstract: The state’s new Democratic governor said he would ease one of the nation’s strictest policies. Iowa will be alone in barring voting by all felons.
snippet: The state’s new Democratic governor said he would ease one of the nation’s strictest policies. Iowa will be alone in barring voting by all felons.
lead_paragraph: Kentucky’s newly elected Democratic governor, Andy Beshear, signed an executive order on Thursday restoring the vote and the right to hold public office to more than 140,000 residents who have completed sentences for nonviolent felonies.

abstract: Famine threatens the lives of up to 5.5 million people in South Sudan, where droughts and flooding have destroyed crops and livestock, compounding "intense political instability", the United Nations warned on Thursday.
snippet: Famine threatens the lives of up to 5.5 million people in South Sudan, where droughts and flooding have destroyed crops and livestock, compounding "intense political instability", the United Nations warned on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: GENEVA — Famine threatens the lives of up to 5.5 million people in South Sudan, where droughts and flooding have destroyed crops and livestock, compounding "intense political instability", the United Nations warned on Thursday.
headline_main: Famine Stalks Millions in South Sudan After Droughts, Floods: U.N.
headline_print_headline: Famine Stalks Millions in South Sudan After Droughts, Floods: U.N.

abstract: Island nations at risk of being erased from the map by rising seas accused rich countries of losing sight of the urgency of the climate crisis on Thursday as a marathon U.N. summit in Madrid entered its final stretch.
snippet: Island nations at risk of being erased from the map by rising seas accused rich countries of losing sight of the urgency of the climate crisis on Thursday as a marathon U.N. summit in Madrid entered its final stretch.
lead_paragraph: MADRID — Island nations at risk of being erased from the map by rising seas accused rich countries of losing sight of the urgency of the climate crisis on Thursday as a marathon U.N. summit in Madrid entered its final stretch.
headline_main: Island States, Threatened by Disasters, Demand Urgent Action at U.N. Climate Talks
headline_print_headline: Island States, Threatened by Disasters, Demand Urgent Action at U.N. Climate Talks

abstract: Kristen Stewart is a picture of gorgeous disintegration in this speculative look at the F.B.I.’s persecution of the actress Jean Seberg.
snippet: Kristen Stewart is a picture of gorgeous disintegration in this speculative look at the F.B.I.’s persecution of the actress Jean Seberg.
lead_paragraph: “A man lit a fire and put me on it,” the actress Jean Seberg (Kristen Stewart) curtly tells her lover, the activist Hakim Jamal (Anthony Mackie), in “Seberg,” a flawed and fascinating film about fame and martyrdom. She’s explaining the burn scars she suffered while playing Joan of Arc in Otto Preminger’s “Saint Joan” (1957), but the comment could as easily serve as this movie’s tagline.

abstract: Elizabeth Warren lashed out Thursday at her moderate Democratic rivals seeking the White House, accusing them of naively accepting Republican calls for unity rather than standing up to the rich while too quickly bending to the whims of their own wealthy donors.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren lashed out Thursday at her moderate Democratic rivals seeking the White House, accusing them of naively accepting Republican calls for unity rather than standing up to the rich while too quickly bending to the whims of their own w...
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — Elizabeth Warren lashed out Thursday at her moderate Democratic rivals seeking the White House, accusing them of naively accepting Republican calls for unity rather than standing up to the rich while too quickly bending to the whims of their own wealthy donors.
headline_main: Warren Slams Moderate Rivals, Laying Bare Ideological Divide
headline_print_headline: Warren Slams Moderate Rivals, Laying Bare Ideological Divide

abstract: President Donald Trump lashed out at 16-year-old climate activist Greta Thunberg on Thursday, a day after she was named by  Time as its Person of the Year, calling her selection “ridiculous."
snippet: President Donald Trump lashed out at 16-year-old climate activist Greta Thunberg on Thursday, a day after she was named by  Time as its Person of the Year, calling her selection “ridiculous."
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump lashed out at 16-year-old climate activist Greta Thunberg on Thursday, a day after she was named by Time as its Person of the Year, calling her selection “ridiculous."
headline_main: Trump Criticizes Climate Activist Thunberg After Time Honor
headline_print_headline: Trump Criticizes Climate Activist Thunberg After Time Honor

abstract: Gamal el Adl's company is one of the most popular television producers in the Middle East. Its gritty soap operas, touching on drug addiction amongst the middle classes, sexual abuse and life in a women's prison, have been hits on TV in Egypt and across the Arab world.
snippet: Gamal el Adl's company is one of the most popular television producers in the Middle East. Its gritty soap operas, touching on drug addiction amongst the middle classes, sexual abuse and life in a women's prison, have been hits on TV in Egypt and ...
lead_paragraph: CAIRO — Gamal el Adl's company is one of the most popular television producers in the Middle East. Its gritty soap operas, touching on drug addiction amongst the middle classes, sexual abuse and life in a women's prison, have been hits on TV in Egypt and across the Arab world.
headline_main: Special Report: Egypt’s Strongman Extends Crackdown to a New Foe-Soap Operas
headline_print_headline: Special Report: Egypt’s Strongman Extends Crackdown to a New Foe-Soap Operas

abstract: Demonstrators defied troops and a curfew after the bill, which would make it easier for some non-Muslim migrants to become citizens, was approved in Parliament.
snippet: Demonstrators defied troops and a curfew after the bill, which would make it easier for some non-Muslim migrants to become citizens, was approved in Parliament.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — Tens of thousands of protesters rioted in three states across India’s northeast, some defying a government curfew and military deployment to demonstrate against the passage of the contentious Citizenship Amendment Bill, which will grant citizenship to thousands of migrants on religious grounds.

abstract: The U.S. Supreme Court may have a conservative majority that includes two justices appointed by President Donald Trump, but his efforts to shield his tax returns and other financial records from scrutiny still face an uncertain future.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. Supreme Court may have a conservative majority that includes two justices appointed by President Donald Trump, but his efforts to shield his tax returns and other financial records from scrutiny still face an uncertain future.
headline_main: Trump Poised for Supreme Court Battle Over Financial Records
headline_print_headline: Trump Poised for Supreme Court Battle Over Financial Records
